The paper discusses a method for improving the optimization process in variational inference, which is a common technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on hierarchical variational methods, which are often used in computer vision and control systems (cs.CV, cs.SY). The method proposed in the paper is inspired by Annealed Importance Sampling, which is a technique commonly used in probabilistic modeling and simulation (cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experiments demonstrating the effectiveness of the proposed method in learning complex distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
